Regarding users' information needs, KGs excel on complex factual queries, but do not cope well with non-factual categories.
 SEs provide support for factual and non-factual categories, but are effective only on simple queries and are inconvenient for questions whose answers do not lie in a single document; similar limitations arise also when structured data needs to be aggregated. LLMs also partially cover both factual and non-factual needs, but 
 are prone to hallucinations and bias, 
 have no formal 
 operators for analytical queries, 
 and can be trapped by false premises in questions.